  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DAM Localised emergency response transition of essential health, WaSH, and protection services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Continuation of lifesaving and comprehensive primary healthcare services, SRH and family planning awareness for 35,000 Rohingya people in settlements</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#xB7;Door-to-door awareness visits on health rights, SRH-family planning, COVID-19 preparedness, also surveillance and referral by Community Health Workers (CHW) following WHO guidelines. (18 CHWs x 3 HH x 24 days x 4 months &#x2013; 5,184 households). 
&#xB7;Operations and maintenance of the 24/7 PHC in Camp 13 and health post in Camp 19 (outpatient and in-patient services with specific focus on emergency stabilisation, IYCF, MHPSS, GBV maternal and neonatal, maintenance of IPC- Infection prevention and control, counselling and referral) and improved accessibility. Target PHC consultation: 14,400 (40 Childbirth); HP target consultation: 9,600</narrative>
  </description>
